        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-12T18:33:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it does - there\u0027s a potential case when a separate reader thread has already started reading the page data from the disk\nin that case it would read it into its own allocated memory, and readDataFromDisk() call here won\u0027t do anything but wait for it to finish reading.\nIn that case we need to free that allocated memory here\nIt\u0027s rare, but I saw it happening",
      "parentUuid": "ea625323_b2018cfa",
      "revId": "0ddc70d1d0c46f372c40ae7f3a2827676af586f7",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
